description._content:
Description: The very last train to operate on standard gauge track hauled by a British Rail steam locomotive, which went from Liverpool-Carlisle and back.
Date: August 11th, 1968
Our Catalogue Reference: RAIL 1057/3537
This image is from the collections of The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. 
For high quality reproductions of any item from our collection please contact our image library: images@nationalarchives.gsi.gov.uk

note._content: It would be interesting to see the photos taken by this lad. He seems keen to get a good viewpoint.
